Raised tissue masses located on the palpebral conjunctiva with a central vessel. Papillae are created by a focal infiltration of inflammatory cells.

Small, dome-shaped nodules without a prominent central vessel located on the conjunctiva. The lymphoid follicles are located in the subendothelial region of the conjunctiva. They consist of a germinal center that contains immature, proliferating lymphocytes, as well as a corona that contains mature lymphocytes and plasma cells.
An abnormal accumulation of protein in the glomerulus.
An abnormal increase in pressure in the pulmonary veins, usually as a result of left atrial hypertension.
Dilatation of the blood vessels of the conjunctiva leading to a red appearance of the sclera.
